<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3770835>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Abyssocladia mucronata sp. nov. A—Holotype. B—Specimen freshly collected during KANADEEP 2. C—View in situ of specimen B (Lat. 23.07303040°, Long. 168.20463888°, depth 1005 m). D—View in situ of the population in the same place (Lat. 23.07308691, Long. 23.07308691°, depth 1010m). E—polished section of a branch, with numerous foreign bodies. F fixation base and stem." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3770835/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3770837>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Abyssocladia mucronata sp. nov. A—Spicules, general view. B—Mucronate style and enlargement of its head and tip. C—Mucronate style of the attachment base. D—Anisotornote and enlargement of the two ends. E—Arcuate cleistochelae, face and dorsal views. F—Growing stages of arcuate cleistochelae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3770837/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

